l podcast hosted bySaturday Night Live's Bowen Yang and actor-comedian Matt Rogers (Fire Island.)\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2254, \"end\": 2258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bowen_Yang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bowen Yang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bowen_Yang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bowen_Yang\"}, {\"begin\": 2377, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Rogers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0008722515684544e-16, \"text\": \"Matt Rogers\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Rogers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Rogers\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fire Island\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2401}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The interview-based podcast will follow the hosts as they learn more about the Olympics from current and former athletes, and celebrity fans.\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2545, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The interview-based podcast\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2431}, {\"ngram\": \"the hosts\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"current and former athletes\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2524}, {\"ngram\": \"celebrity fans\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Listeners can follow along to learn and celebrate the athletes, city, and culture of the Paris Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Listeners\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2555}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2608}, {\"ngram\": \"city\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2614}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2627}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The podcast is set to launch weekly episodes in late June stretching from before the Olympic Opening Ceremony and continuing through the Closing Ceremony in August, distributed by iHeartPodcasts and available on the iHeartRadio app and everywhere podcasts are heard.\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2749, \"end\": 2765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9854225032470678, \"rank\": 0.0146867016050372, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics_opening_ceremony\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The podcast\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2667}, {\"ngram\": \"weekly episodes\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2700}, {\"ngram\": \"late June\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2713}, {\"ngram\": \"the Closing Ceremony\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2809}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2819}, {\"ngram\": \"iHeartPodcasts\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2850}, {\"ngram\": \"the iHeartRadio app\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2887}, {\"ngram\": \"podcasts\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 2911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, as part of this collaboration with NBCU, iHeartMedia will produce Olympic-themed episodes for some of its most popular educational podcasts, includingStuff You Missed in History ClassandRidiculous History.\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 3143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2973, \"end\": 2977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wik